      "content": "While some argue that high-density living sacrifices green space, the reality is that thoughtful density allows for the *integration* of parks and public amenities within the urban fabric. The push for density is not merely inevitable; it is the necessary, pragmatic response to the environmental and logistical crises of modern urbanization. The opposition often stems from NIMBYism, which prioritizes outdated suburban ideals over sustainable, functional city living.",
